    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/2862: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. For Walmsley.<note n="49" xml:id="d321fn49">Walter N. Walmsley, Jr.,
                        Assistant Chief, Division of the American Republics.</note> The Minister of
                        Hacienda,<note n="50" xml:id="d321fn50">Oscar García Montes.</note> López
                        Castro<note n="51" xml:id="d321fn51">Cuban Secretary of the
                        Presidency.</note> and Subsecretary of Defense, Perez Benitoa will leave
                    Wednesday morning by airplane for Miami probably [apparent omission] the Cuban
                    Embassy of the exact hour of arrival in Washington).</p>
                <p>The Minister of Hacienda wishes to take up the various financial matters under
                    study by our Treasury officials and also final conclusion of the 25 million
                    dollars credit operation López Castro participating in the latter negotiation.
                    According to the Minister of State<note n="52" xml:id="d321fn52">José Manuel
                        Cortina.</note> the Cuban Government will seek certain changes in the
                    current credit draft but Cortina expressed the opinion that no changes in
                    principal are contemplated and that he hopes final agreement can be reached
                    within a very few days.</p>
                <p>López Castro has been instructed urgently to supplement Concheso’s<note n="53"
                        xml:id="d321fn53">Aurelio F. Concheso, Cuban Ambassador in the United
                        States.</note> representation concerning shipping and will also desire to
                    discuss sugar.</p>
                <p>The Subsecretary of Defense has been directed by the President to endeavor to
                    expedite delivery of at least some of the material now on order (please see my
                    telegram No. 74, February 21, 3 a.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d321fn54">Not printed;
                        for correspondence on the problems of hemisphere defense, see <ref
                            target="#pg_253">pp. 253</ref> ff.</note>).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
